@GLMS.API_HostAddress = http://localhost:5291

### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  AUTH
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


### Login — returns JWT (8hr expiry). Default seed: admin / Admin@1234
# @name login
POST {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json


{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "Admin@1234"
}


### Capture the token from the login response for use in subsequent requests
@authToken = {{login.response.body.token}}




### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  DASHBOARD
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


### Get dashboard summary (aggregate counts) — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/dashboard




### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  CLIENTS
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


### Get all clients — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/clients




### Get a single client by ID — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/clients/1




### Create a new client — Requires JWT
# @name createClient
POST {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/clients
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


{
  "name": "Northbound Carriers Ltd",
  "contractDetails": "Cross-border road freight",
  "region": "EMEA"
}




### Update an existing client — Requires JWT
PUT {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/clients/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


{
  "name": "Acme Freight Ltd",
  "contractDetails": "Air & sea freight — updated",
  "region": "EMEA"
}




### Delete a client (only if it has no contracts) — Requires JWT
DELETE {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/clients/99
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}




### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  CONTRACTS
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


### Get all contracts (no filters) — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/contracts




### Get contracts filtered by status — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/contracts?status=Active




### Get contracts filtered by date range — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/contracts?from=2024-01-01&to=2024-12-31




### Get contracts filtered by status AND date range — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/contracts?status=Active&from=2024-01-01&to=2024-12-31




### Get a single contract by ID (includes service requests) — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/1




### Create a new contract — Requires JWT
# @name createContract
POST {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/contracts
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


{
  "clientId": 1,
  "startDate": "2026-01-01",
  "endDate": "2027-01-01",
  "status": "Draft",
  "serviceLevel": "Priority 2 — 8-hour response"
}




### Update all fields of an existing contract — Requires JWT
PUT {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/1
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


{
  "clientId": 1,
  "startDate": "2024-01-01",
  "endDate": "2025-01-01",
  "status": "Active",
  "serviceLevel": "Priority 1 — 4-hour response (updated)"
}




### Update ONLY the status of a contract (approve/decline/expire/hold) — Requires JWT
PATCH {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/1/status
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


{
  "status": "Active"
}




### Upload a signed PDF agreement for a contract — Requires JWT
# NOTE: Adjust the file path below to a real PDF on your machine before sending.
POST {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/1/agreement
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----GlmsBoundary


----GlmsBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="signed-agreement.pdf"
Content-Type: application/pdf


< ./sample-files/signed-agreement.pdf
----GlmsBoundary--




### Download the signed agreement PDF for a contract — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/1/agreement




### Delete a contract and its agreement file — Requires JWT
DELETE {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/contracts/99
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}




### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  SERVICE REQUESTS
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


### Get all service requests — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/servicerequests




### Get a single service request by ID — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/servicerequests/1




### Create a new service request — Requires JWT
### Validates that the parent contract is Active or Draft, then converts USD → ZAR
# @name createServiceRequest
POST {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/servicerequests
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


{
  "contractId": 1,
  "description": "Emergency container re-routing — Durban to Cape Town",
  "costUsd": 750.00
}




### Update the status of a service request — Requires JWT
PATCH {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/servicerequests/1/status
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


{
  "status": "InProgress"
}




### Delete a service request — Requires JWT
DELETE {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/servicerequests/99
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}




### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  CURRENCY
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


### Get the current live USD to ZAR exchange rate — No auth required
GET {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/currency/rate




### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###  NEGATIVE / VALIDATION TESTS
###  Useful for confirming workflow rules and auth enforcement.
### ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


### Should return 401 — no Authorization header on a JWT-protected endpoint
POST {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/clients
Content-Type: application/json


{
  "name": "Should Fail",
  "contractDetails": "No token provided",
  "region": "ZA"
}




### Should return 400 — cannot create a service request on an Expired contract
### (Assumes contract #2 in seed data has Status = Expired)
POST {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/servicerequests
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json


{
  "contractId": 2,
  "description": "Should be rejected — contract is Expired",
  "costUsd": 100.00
}




### Should return 401 — invalid login credentials
POST {{GLMS.API_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json


{
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "WrongPassword123"
}


